Q7.
An NFA has two states: q0 (start) and q1 (accept).  
Transitions:
- From q0 on input a → q1
- From q1 on input b or c → q1

This NFA accepts strings of the form a(b|c)*.  
Write a C program that simulates this NFA (by tracking the set of current states) and prints whether a given input string is accepted.

// Q7: NFA simulation using state sets
#include <iostream>
#include <set>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    string s;
    cin >> s;

    set<int> cur = {0}; // q0

    for (char c : s) {
        set<int> next;

        for (int q : cur) {
            if (q == 0 && c == 'a') next.insert(1);
            if (q == 1 && (c == 'b' || c == 'c')) next.insert(1);
        }

        cur = next;
        if (cur.empty()) break;
    }

    if (cur.count(1)) cout << "Accepted\n";
    else cout << "Rejected\n";
}

Input: abcbc
Output: Accepted
